cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for brain magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) analysis, which falls under the computer vision domain. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the architectures and strategies used in these CNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of CNNs for medical image analysis, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
